01/03/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Somali pirates have released a Greek cargo ship with 19 crew members aboard after demanding a ransom two months ago. 
"We can confirm that the Greek ship Navios Apollon, sailing under the Panamanian flag, has been released this morning," a Greek official announced on Sunday (February 28th). 
The ship had 18 Filipinos and 1 Greek citizen onboard. 
The amount of the ransom was not disclosed. 
(AP, BBC, Reuters - 28/02/10)
